description: Are you an aspiring entrepreneur on campus and wondering if forming an LLC is the right step for your business? Join Max Hayden, an experienced entrepreneur and board member of the Rutgers Entrepreneurial Society, and Ansh Gandhi, another experienced entrepreneur and board member of the Rutgers Personal Finance Club for an insightful event designed to educate student entrepreneurs about Limited Liability Companies (LLCs) and other corporate structures for entrepreneur-founded businesses. Event Highlights:  Is an LLC Right for You?  Understand the key considerations for choosing an LLC over other business structures, including sole proprietorships and corporations.    Benefits and Responsibilities of Forming an LLC  Learn about the advantages of forming an LLC in New Jersey, such as personal liability protection, and discover the ongoing responsibilities of maintaining your LLC’s compliance.    Tax Implications for LLCs  Get a clear breakdown of how forming an LLC can affect your taxes, including federal and state tax obligations, deductions, and more.    How to Form an LLC in New Jersey  We will guide you step by step through the process of setting up an LLC in New Jersey, from filing paperwork to handling registration fees.     With their extensive experience in forming multiple LLCs and building successful ventures, Max Hayden and Ansh Gandhi will provide actionable insights and practical advice for student entrepreneurs looking to structure their businesses properly. Don’t miss this opportunity to learn the foundations of forming and running a legal business entity in New Jersey. Who Should Attend?  Rutgers students interested in entrepreneurship Aspiring business founders exploring corporate structures Entrepreneurs curious about the benefits of LLCs  Reserve your spot today and take the first step toward formalizing your business! Parking passes and REAL points are available for attendees.
name: Exploring LLCs and Corporate Structures for Entrepreneurs
organizationNames: Entrepreneurial Society (Rutgers)
Rutgers Personal Finance Club

description: Join the Center for Women in the Arts at Douglass for an exhibition reception and artist’s lecture by the 2024-2025 Lebowitz Artist-in-Residence, Leah DeVun! DeVun is an award-winning photographer, scholar, and Rutgers Professor whose scholarship, artwork, and curatorial practice reflect her interests in LGBTQ history, science and medicine, religion, archival practice, utopian communities, and gender and the body.   This is a community-wide event and all Rutgers students, faculty, and staff are invited to attend. For Douglass students, this experience counts towards the R3: Douglass Discovery/Career Pathways curriculum requirement.Light refreshments provided.   Event Schedule: 5:00-5:30pm Exhibition Reception5:30-6:30pm Artist's Lecture   Exhibition Details:On view through March 14, 2025 in the Mary H. Dana Women Artists Series Galleries at Douglass LibraryLeah DeVun: ResemblanceThrough photographs of her trans partner and their son, this exhibition offers a window into queer life challenging public discourse that often centers anti-LGBTQ pain and violence. Learn more about DeVun’s residency and work here.
location: Douglass Library, Mabel Smith Douglass Room
name: Leah DeVun: Exhibition Reception & Artist's Lecture
